S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Beacon shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shape a beacon exhibits

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stake, pole, perch, post
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an elongated wood or metal pole, embedded in the bottom to serve as a navigational aid or a support for a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: withy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tree without roots stuck or spoiled into the bottom of the sea to serve as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: beacon tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a solid structure of the order of 10 metres in height used as a navigational aid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lattice beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a structure consisting of strips of metal or wood crossed or interlaced to form a structure to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pile beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a long heavy timber(s) or section(s) of steel, wood, concrete, etc., forced into the seabed to serve as an aid to navigation or as a support for an aid to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cairn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mound of stones, usually conical or pyramidal, raised specifically for maritime navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: buoyant beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tall spar-like beacon fitted with a permanently submerged buoyancy chamber, the lower end of the body is secured to seabed sinker either by a flexible joint or by a cable under tension.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Building shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The specific shape of the building.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: high-rise building
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a building having many storeys.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pyramid
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a polyhedron of which one face is a polygon of any number of sides, and the other faces are triangles with a common vertex.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cylindrical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: shaped like a cylinder, which is a solid geometrical figure generated by straight lines fixed in direction and describing with one of its points a closed curve, especially a circle.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: spherical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: shaped like a sphere, which is a body the surface of which is at all points equidistant from the centre.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cubic
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a shape the sides of which are six equal squares a regular hexahedron.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Buoy shape
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The shape a buoy exhibits
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The principal shapes are those recommended in the International Association of Lighthouse Authorities - IALA System.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: conical (nun, ogival)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has approximately the shape or the appearance of a pointed cone with the point upwards.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: can (cylindrical)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the shape of a cylinder, or a truncated cone that approximates to a cylinder, with a flat end uppermost.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: spherical
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the shape of a part of a sphere.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pillar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure is a narrow vertical structure, pillar or lattice tower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: spar (spindle)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a pole, or of a very long cylinder, floating upright.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: barrel (tun)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the upper part of the body above the water-line, or the greater part of the superstructure, has the form of a barrel or cylinder floating horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: super-buoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a very large buoy, generally more than 5m in diameter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ice buoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a specially constructed shuttle shaped buoy which is used in ice conditions.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Buried depth
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The depth below the sea bed to which an object is buried.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The unit of measure is defined in the HUNI subfield of the DSPM record or in the HUNITS attribute of the M_UNIT meta object class, e.g., metre (m). The resolution is 0.1 m or 0.1 ft.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Call sign
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The designated call-sign of a radio station.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of airport/airfield
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of airport/airfield based on the primary aircraft and user group.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: military aeroplane airport
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a large military airfield usually equipped with a control tower, hangars and accommodation for the receiving and discharging of passengers or cargo.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: civil aeroplane airport
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a large airfield usually equipped with a control tower, hangars and accommodation for the receiving and discharging of passengers or cargo.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: military heliport
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a landing place for helicopters controlled by the military.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: civil heliport
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a landing place for helicopters, often the roof of a building.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: glider airfield
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area of land set aside for the take-off and landing of gliders.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: small planes airfield
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area of land set aside for the take-off and landing of small aeroplanes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: emergency airfield
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area of land set aside for the take-off and landing of aeroplanes or helicopters in times of emergency.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of anchorage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an area where diffrent usetypes of vessel can remain static.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: unrestricted anchorage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which vessels anchor or may anchor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deep water anchorage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which vessels of deep draught anchor or may anchor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tanker anchorage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which tankers anchor or may anchor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: explosives anchorage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area set apart for anchored ships discharging or receiving explosives.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: quarantine anchorage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area where a vessel anchors when satisfying quarantine regulations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sea-plane anchorage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which sea-planes anchor or may anchor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: small craft anchorage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which yachts and small boats anchor or may anchor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: small craft mooring area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which yachts and small boats moor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: anchorage for periods up to 24 hours
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which vessels anchor or may anchor for periods of up to 24 hours.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: anchorage for a limited period of time
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which vessels may anchor for a period of time not to exceed a specific limit.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of bridge
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of structures spanning and providing passage over a gap or barrier, such as a river or roadway

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fixed bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a bridge having permanent horizontal and vertical alignment.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: opening bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a bridge that is closed when set for carrying road traffic and open when set to permit marine traffic to pass through the waterway it crosses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: swing bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a movable bridge (or span thereof) which rotates in a horizontal plane about a vertical pivot to allow the passage of vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lifting bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a movable bridge (or span thereof) which is capable of being lifted vertically to allow vessels to pass beneath.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bascule bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a counterpoise bridge rotated in a vertical plane about an axis at one or both ends.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pontoon bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a fixed floating bridge supported by pontoons.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: drawBridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a general name for bridges of which part or the entire span of the bridge may be raised or drawn aside to allow ships to pass through.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: transporter bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a bridge that has towers on each side of the waterway connected by a girder system on which a carriage runs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: foot bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a bridge structure used only for pedestrian traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: viaduct
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a long bridge consisting of a series of beams, spans or girders (of steel, timber or concrete) supported on towers or piers and used to carry a road, railroad, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: aqueduct
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a bridge supporting an artificially elevated channel, for the conveyance of water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: suspension bridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a fixed bridge consisting of either a roadway or a truss suspended from two or more cables which pass over towers and are anchored by backstays to a firm foundation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of built-up area
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Human settlement classification

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: urban area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area predominantly occupied by man-made structures used for residential, commercial, and industrial purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: settlement
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a small collection of dwellings in a remote area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: village
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a collection of houses in a rural district, usually smaller than a town.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: town
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any considerable collection of dwellings and other buildings larger than a village, but not incorporated as a city.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: city
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a major town inhabited by a large permanent community with all essential services.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: holiday village
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a collection of smaller houses (cottages, mobile homes etc.) which is mainly populated on a seasonal basis.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of cable
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the cable based on the services provided.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: power line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a cable used for the supply of electricity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: transmission line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: multiple un-insulated cables usually supported by steel lattice towers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: telephone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a cable used for the transmission of telephone signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: telegraph
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a cable used for the transmission of telegraph signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mooring cable/chain
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a cable or chain used to secure a mooring buoy or other floating structure.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of canal
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an artificial waterway used for travel, drainage, or irrigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: transportation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a canal used for navigation as part of a transport system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: drainage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a canal used to drain excess water from surrounding land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: irrigation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a canal used to supply water for the purpose of irrigation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of cardinal mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Cardinal marks are classified according to the quadrant of space they occupy.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Cardinal marks are used in conjunction with the compass to indicate where a mariner will find safe navigable water. Cardinal marks do not have a distinctive shape but are normally pillar or spar. They are always painted in yellow and black horizontal bands and their distinctive double cone top-marks are always black. (Note that such top-marks are encoded as separate TOPMAR objects). Cardinal marks may also have a special system of flashing white lights and if such lights are fitted they are encoded as separate LIGHTS objects.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: north cardinal mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing NW-NE taken from the point of interest it should be passed to the north side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: east cardinal mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing NE-SE taken from the point of interest it should be passed to the east side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: south cardinal mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing SE-SW taken from the point of interest it should be passed to the south side of the mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: west cardinal mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Quadrant bounded by the true bearing SW-NW taken from the point of interest it should be passed to the west side of the mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of checkpoint
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of a place where vehicles or travellers are stopped for identification or inspection

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: custom
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an office, especially in ports, at which customs dues are collected or administrated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of coastline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Physical condition of the coastline

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: steep coast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a coast backed by rock or earth cliffs, gives a good radar return and is useful for visual identification from a considerable distance off, where cliffs alternate with low lying coast along the shoreline.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flat coast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a level coast with no obvious topographic features.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sandy shore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a shoreline area made up of sand, i.e., loose material consisting of small but easily distinguishable, separate grains, between 0.0625 and 2.000 millimetres in diameter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stony shore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a shoreline area made up of rock and rock fragments ranging in size from pebbles and gravel to boulders or large rock masses.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shingly shore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a shoreline area made up of rounded, often flat waterworn rock fragments larger than approximately 16 millimetres.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: glacier, seaward end
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: projecting seaward extension of glacier, usually afloat.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mangrove
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: one of several genera of tropical trees or shrubs which produce many prop roots and grow along low lying coasts into shallow water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: marshy shore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a shoreline area made up of spongy land saturated with water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: coral reef
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a reef, often of large extent, composed chiefly of coral and its derivatives.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ice coast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a vertical cliff forming the seaward edge of an ice shelf, ranging in height from 2m to 50m or more above sea level.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shelly shore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a shoreline area made up of shells, i.e., made up of the hard outside covering of marine animals.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of conveyor
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of conveyor used for moving goods from one location to another.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: aerial cableway (telepheric)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a conveyor along which material or people are transported by means of overhead cables supporting buckets, cable cars, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: belt conveyor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a conveyor along which material or people are transported by means of a moving belt.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flume
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an artificial channel, usually an inclined chute or trough, for carrying water to furnish power, transport logs down a mountainside, etc.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of crane
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of machines used for hoisting and moving heavy objects

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: container crane/gantry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a high speed, shore-based crane used in the lift-on/lift-off operation of specially constructed containers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sheerlegs
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tripodal structure used in dockyards and harbours for stepping masts or lifting loads in to and out of vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: travelling crane
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a crane mounted on rails (track) that can move (usually parallel to the wharf face) in order to load and unload cargo vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: A-frame
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a type of crane shaped like the letter 'A'.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of dam
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of a structure acting as barrier to water flow

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: weir
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a dam erected across a river to raise the level of the water. A fence of stakes set in a river or along the shore as a trap for fish.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dam
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a barrier to check or confine anything in motion particularly one constructed to hold back water and raise its level to form a reservoir, or to prevent flooding.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flood barrage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an opening dam across a channel which, when required, is closed to control flood waters.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of distance mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of fixed and virtual distance marks

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: distance mark not physically installed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a point at which a distance from an origin along a feature is given for information, but at which no specific marker exists.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: visible mark, pole
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a point at which a distance from an origin along a feature is given for information and which is marked by a pole.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: visible mark, board
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a point at which a distance from an origin along a feature is given for information and which is marked by a board.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: visible mark, unknown shape
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a point at which a distance from an origin along a feature is given for information and which is physically marked, but the shape of the mark is not known or not given.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of dock
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of vessel dock

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tidal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a dock which is open to the sea and in which the water level is affected by tides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: non-tidal (wet dock)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a dock in which water can be maintained at any level by closing a gate when the water is at the desired level.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of fence/wall
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of a physical boudary

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fence
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a man-made barrier of relatively light structure used as an enclosure or boundary.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: hedge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a continuous growth of shrubbery planted as a fence, a boundary or a wind break.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wall
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a solid man-made barrier of generally heavy material used as an enclosure, boundary, or for protection.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of ferry
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the manoeuvrability of the ferry vessel, not the various types of ferry vessel.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The value 'cable ferry' indicates a ferry that follows a fixed route guided by a cable. A cable ferry may hinder the flow of other traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: 'free-moving' ferry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a ferry which may have routes that vary with weather, tide and traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cable ferry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a ferry that follows a fixed route guided by a cable.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ice ferry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a winter-time ferry which crosses a lead.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of fishing facility
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of fishing facility provided based on different fishing methods.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fishing stake
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a pole or stake placed in shallow water to outline a fishing ground or to catch fish

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fish trap
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a structure (usually portable) for catching fish

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fish weir
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a fence of stakes or stones set in a river or along the shore to trap fish

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tunny net
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a net built at sea for catching tunny

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of fog signal
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the various means of generating the fog signal.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The classification 'horn' is the generic term for fog signals 'nautophone', 'reed' and 'tyfon'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: explosive
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a signal produced by the firing of explosive charges.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: diaphone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a diaphone uses compressed air and generally emits a powerful low-pitched sound, which often concludes with a brief sound of suddenly lowered pitch, termed the 'grunt'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: siren
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a siren uses compressed air and exists in a variety of types which differ considerably in their sound and power.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: nautophone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a horn having a diaphragm oscillated by electricity

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: reed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a reed uses compressed air and emits a weak, high pitched sound.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tyfon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a diaphragm horn which operates under the influence of compressed air or steam

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bell
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a ringing sound with a short range.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: whistle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a distinctive sound made by a jet of air passing through an orifice.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: gong
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a sound produced by vibration of a disc when struck.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: horn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a horn uses compressed air or electricity to vibrate a diaphragm and exists in a variety of types which differ greatly in their sound and power.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of fortified structure
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the diffrent types of fortified structure

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: castle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a large fortified building or structure

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fort
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a fortified enclosure, building, or position able to be defended against an enemy

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: battery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a fortified structure on which artillery is mounted

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: blockhouse
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a concrete structure strengthened to give protection against enemy fire, with apertures to allow defensive gunfire

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: martello tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a round fort for coastal defence.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: redoubt
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an outwork or fieldwork usually square or polygonal and without flanking defences.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of gate
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of a structure that can be swung, drawn, or lowered to block an entrance or a passageway

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flood barrage gate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an opening gate used to control flood water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: caisson
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a steel structure used for closing the entrance of locks, wet and dry docks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lock gate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: lock gates are the massive hinged doors at each end of a lock.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dyke gate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an opening gate in a dyke.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sluice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a sliding gate or other contrivance for changing the level of a body of water by controlling the flow into or out of it.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of harbour facility
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of habour use
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A terminal provides facilities for handling particular forms of cargo (IHO Dictionary, S-32, 5th Edition, 5343).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: roRo terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a terminal for roll-on roll-off ferries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ferry terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a terminal for passenger and vehicle ferries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fishing harbour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a harbour with facilities for fishing boats.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: yacht harbour/marina
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a harbour with facilities for small boats and yachts

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: naval base
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a centre of operations for naval vessels

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tanker terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a terminal for the bulk handling of liquid cargoes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: passenger terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a terminal for the loading and unloading of passengers.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shipyard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where ships are built or repaired

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: container terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a terminal for container ships.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bulk terminal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a terminal for the handling of bulk materials such as iron ore, coal, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ship lift
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a platform powered by synchronous electric motors used to lift vessels (larger than boats) in and out of the water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: straddle carrier
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wheeled vehicle designed to lift and carry containers or vessels within its own framework.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: service harbour
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a harbour within which the floating equipment (dredges, tugs .) of harbour services are stationed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of hulk
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an old or unseaworthy ship used for a new fuction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: floating restaurant
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a permanently moored floating structure, such as an old ship, used as a restaurant.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: historic ship
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a ship of historical interest permanently moored as a tourist attraction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: floating museum
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a permanently moored floating structure, such as an old ship, used as a museum.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: floating accommodation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a permanently moored floating structure, such as an old ship, used for accommodation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: floating breakwater
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a permanently moored floating structure, often constructed from old ships, used as a breakwater.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: casino boat
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a permanently moored floating structure, such as an old ship, used as a casino boat

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: training vessel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a permanently moored floating structure, often constructed from old ships, used

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of ice
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of ice
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Ice is the topic of another group and is subject to a future extension to this document.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fast ice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: sea ice which remains fast, generally in the position where originally formed, and which may attain a considerable thickness.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: glacier
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mass of snow and ice continuously moving from higher to lower ground or, if afloat, continuously spreading.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: polar ice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: sea ice that is more than one year old (in contrast to winter ice). The WMO code defines polar ice as any sea ice more than one year old and more than 3 metres thick.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of installation buoy
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of fixed installation buoy

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: catenary anchor leg mooring (CALM)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: incorporates a large buoy which remains on the surface at all times and is moored by 4 or more anchors. Mooring hawsers and cargo hoses lead from a turntable on top of the buoy, so that the buoy does not turn as the ship swings to wind and stream.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: single buoy mooring (SBM)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mooring structure used by tankers to load and unload in port approaches or in offshore oil and gas fields. The size of the structure can vary between a large mooring buoy and a manned floating structure. Also known as single point mooring (SPM)

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of landmark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of prominent cultural and natural features in the landscape

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cairn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a mound of stones, usually conical or pyramidal, raised as a landmark or to designate a point of importance in surveying.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cemetery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area of land for burying the dead.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: chimney
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a vertical structure containing a passage or flue for discharging smoke and gases.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dish aerial
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a parabolic aerial for the receipt and transmission of high frequency radio signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flagstaff (flagpole)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a staff or pole on which flags are raised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flare stack
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tall structure used for burning-off waste oil or gas. Normally showing a flame and located at refineries.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mast
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a straight vertical piece of timber or a hollow cylinder.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wind sock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tapered fabric sleeve mounted so as to catch and swing with the wind, thus indicating the wind direction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: monument
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a structure erected or maintained as a memorial to a person or event.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: column (pillar)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a cylindrical or slightly tapering body of considerably greater length than diameter erected vertically.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: memorial plaque
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a slab of metal, usually ornamented, erected as a memorial to a person or event.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: obelisk
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tapering shaft usually of stone or concrete, square or rectangular in section, with a pyramidal apex.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: statue
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a representation of a human, animal or fantasy figure in marble, bronze, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cross
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a monument, or other structure in form of a cross.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dome
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a landmark comprising a hemispherical or spheroidal shaped structure

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: radar scanner
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a device used for directing a radar beam through a search pattern

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively tall structure which may be used for observation, support, storage or communication etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: windmill
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a wind driven system of vanes attached to a tower like structure (excluding wind-generated power plants).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: windmotor
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a modern structure for the use of windpower.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: spire/minaret
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tall conical or pyramid-shaped structure often built on the roof or tower of a building, especially a church or mosque.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: large rock or boulder on land
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an isolated rocky formation or a single large stone

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: triangulation Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a recoverable point on the earth, whose geographic position has been determined by angular methods with geodetic instruments. A triangulation point is a selected point, which has been marked with a station mark, or it is a conspicuous natural or artificial feature. Also called trigonometric station or triangulation station.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: boundary Mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a marker identifying the location of a surveyed boundary line.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: observation wheel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a bloody big Ferris Wheel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: torii
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a gate located in a Shinto shrine.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of land region
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: General terms for describing landscapes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fen
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a type of bog, especially a low-lying area, wholly or partly covered with water and dominated by grasslike plants, grasses, sedges and reeds.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: marsh
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area of wet, often spongy ground that is subject to frequent flooding or tidal inundations, but not considered to be continually under water. It is characterized by the growth of non woody plants and by the lack of trees.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: moor/bog
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: wet spongy ground consisting of decaying vegetation, which retains stagnant water, too soft to bear the weight of any heavy body.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: heathland
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tract of wasteland peat bog, usually covered by a low scrubby growth, but may have scattered small open water holes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mountain range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a series of connected and aligned mountains or mountain ridges.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lowlands
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: low and relatively level land at a lower elevation than adjoining areas.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: canyon lands
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively narrow, deep depression with steep sides, the bottom of which generally has a continuous slope.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: paddy field
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a piece of land set aside for crops which are periodically flooded (e.g. rice paddy).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: agricultural land
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: areas used for cultivation of the soil, the breeding of livestock etc. and general farming.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: savanna/grassland
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a large area of relatively flat natural pasture.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: parkland
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a piece of ground kept for ornament and/or recreation or maintained in its natural state as a public property or area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: swamp
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area of spongy land saturated with water. It may have a shallow covering of water, usually with a considerable amount of vegetation appearing above the surface.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: landslide
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (or landslip). The sliding down of a mass of land on a mountain or cliff-side land which has so fallen.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lava flow
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the substance that results from the cooling of molten rock.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: saltpan
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: shallow pools of brackish water used for the natural evaporation of sea water to obtain salt.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: crater
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: bowl-shaped cavity, at the summit or on the side of a volcano.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cave
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a natural subterranean chamber or series of chambers open to the earths surface.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: rock column or pinnacle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any high tower or spire-shaped pillar of rock, alone or cresting a summit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: cay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a small insular feature usually with scant vegetation usually of sand or coral. Often applied to smaller coral shoals.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of lateral mark
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of lateral buoys
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: There are two international buoyage regions, A and B, between which lateral marks differ. The buoyage region is encoded using the separate attribute MARSYS. When top-marks, retro reflectors and/or lights are fitted to these marks, they are encoded as separate objects.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: port-hand lateral mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: indicates the port boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the 'conventional direction of buoyage'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: starboard-hand lateral mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: indicates the starboard boundary of a navigational channel or suggested route when proceeding in the 'conventional direction of buoyage'.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: preferred channel to starboard lateral mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: at a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the 'conventional direction of buoyage', the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified port-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: preferred channel to port lateral mark
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: at a point where a channel divides, when proceeding in the 'conventional direction of buoyage', the preferred channel (or primary route) is indicated by a modified starboard-hand lateral mark.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of light
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of diffrent light types
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Marine light (a light intended primarily for marine navigation) is not included in the above list. All lights are considered to be marine lights unless the attribute 'category of light' indicates otherwise.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: leading light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light associated with other lights so as to form a leading line to be followed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: aero light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an aero light is established for aeronautical navigation and may be of higher power than marine lights and visible from well offshore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flood light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a broad beam light used to illuminate a structure or area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: strip light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light whose source has a linear form generally horizontal, which can reach a length of several metres.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: subsidiary light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light placed on or near the support of a main light and having a special use in navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: spotlight
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a powerful light focused so as to illuminate a small area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: front
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: rear
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: upper
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: term used with leading lights to describe the position of the light on the lead as viewed from seaward.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: emergency
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light available as a backup to a main light which will be illuminated should the main light fail.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bearing light
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a light which enables its approximate bearing to be obtained without the use of a compass.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: horizontally disposed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a group of lights of identical character and almost identical position, that are disposed horizontally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: vertically disposed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a group of lights of identical character and almost identical position, that are disposed vertically.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of marine farm/culture
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an area of water devoted to the raising, breeding, or production of a specific aquatic animal

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: crustaceans
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: hard shelled animals, for example crabs or lobsters.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: oysters/mussels
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: edible bivalve molluscs.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fish
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: vertebrate cold blooded animal with gills, living in water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: seaweed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the general name for marine plants of the Algae class which grow in long narrow ribbons.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pearl culture farm
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area where pearls are artificially cultivated.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of military practice area
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of area by military use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: torpedo exercise area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which exercises are carried out with torpedoes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: submarine exercise area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which submarine exercises are carried out.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: firing danger area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: areas for bombing and missile exercises.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mine laying practice area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which mine laying exercises are carried out.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: small arms firing range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area for shooting pistols, rifles and machine guns etc. at a target.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of mooring/warping facility
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A place or structure to which a vessel can be secured

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dolphin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a post or group of posts, which may support a deck, used for mooring or warping a vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deviation dolphin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a post or group of posts, which a vessel may swing around for compass adjustment.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bollard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: small shaped post, mounted on a wharf or dolphin used to secure ship's lines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tie-up wall
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tie-up wall is a section of wall designated for tying-up vessels awaiting transit. Bollards and mooring devices are available for both large and small ships.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: post or pile
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a long heavy timber or section of steel, wood, concrete, etc., forced into the seabed to serve as a mooring facility.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: chain/wire/cable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a connection between two independent objects e.g. a buoy and pile or between two buoys used as a mooring facility.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mooring buoy
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a buoy secured to the bottom by permanent moorings with means for mooring a vessel by use of its anchor chain or mooring lines.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of navigation line
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of route guidence given to vessels

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: clearing line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a straight line that marks the boundary between a safe and a dangerous area or that passes clear of a navigational danger.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: transit line
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a line passing through one or more fixed marks.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: leading line bearing a recommended track
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a line passing through one or more clearly defined objects, along the path of which a vessel can approach safely up to a certain distance off.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of obstruction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of objects that impead movement

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: snag/stump
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tree, branch or broken pile embedded in the ocean floor, river or lake bottom and not visible on the surface, forming thereby a hazard to vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wellhead
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a submarine structure projecting some distance above the seabed and capping a temporarily abandoned or suspended oil or gas well.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: diffuser
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a structure on an outfall through which liquids are discharged. The structure will usually project above the level of the outfall and can be an obstruction to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: crib
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a permanent structure set in the water, framed with wooden beams and filled with rocks or boulders. They are used to anchor log booms or support other constructions, e.g. submerged outfalls, diffusers etc. They may always be dry, submerged or cover and uncover.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fish haven
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: areas established by private interests, usually sport fishermen, to simulate natural reefs and wrecks that attract fish. The reefs are constructed by dumping assorted junk in areas which may be of very small extent or may stretch a considerable distance along a depth contour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: foul area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area of numerous unidentified dangers to navigation. The area serves as a warning to the mariner that all dangers are not identified individually and that navigation through the area may be hazardous. Commonly used to encode areas behind danger lines on navigation charts.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: foul ground
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: areas over which it is safe to navigate but which should be avoided for anchoring, taking the ground or ground fishing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ice boom
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: floating barriers, anchored to the bottom, used to deflect the path of floating ice in order to prevent the obstruction of locks, intakes, etc., and to prevent damage to bridge piers and other structures.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ground tackle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: equipment such as anchors, concrete blocks, chains and cables, etc., used to position floating structures such as trot and mooring buoys etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: boom
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a floating barrier used to protect a river or harbour mouth or to create a sheltered area for storage purposes.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of offshore platform
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an offshore raised structure

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: oil derrick/rig
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a temporary mobile structure, either fixed or floating, used in the exploration stages of oil and gas fields.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: production platform
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a term used to indicate a permanent offshore structure equipped to control the flow of oil or gas. It does not include entirely submarine structures.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: observation/research platform
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a platform from which one's surroundings or events can be observed, noted or recorded such as for scientific study.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: articulated loading platform (ALP)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a metal lattice tower, buoyant at one end and attached at the other by a universal joint to a concrete filled base on the sea bed. The platform may be fitted with a helicopter platform, emergency accommodation and hawser/hose retrieval.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: single anchor leg mooring (SALM)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a rigid frame or tube with a buoyancy device at its upper end , secured at its lower end to a universal joint on a large steel or concrete base resting on the sea bed, and at its upper end to a mooring buoy by a chain or wire.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mooring tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a platform secured to the sea bed and surmounted by a turntable to which ships moor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: artificial island
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a man-made structure usually built for the exploration or exploitation of marine resources, marine scientific research, tidal observations, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: floating production, storage and offloading vessel (FPSO)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an offshore oil/gas facility consisting of a moored tanker/barge by which the product is extracted, stored and exported.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: accommodation platform
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a platform used primarily for eating, sleeping and recreation purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: navigation, communication and control buoy (NCCB)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a floating structure with control room, power and storage facilities, attached to the sea bed by a flexible pipeline and cables.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: offshore wind farm
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a collection of wind motors that are collocated and are organized as a single power generation unit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wave farm
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a collection of collocated devices which harness wave energy and are organized as a single power generation unit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: current farm
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a collection of collocated devices which harness tidal energy and are organized as a single power generation unit.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tank farm
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a collection of collocated large-capacity tanks in which petroleum, natural gas, or liquid petrochemicals are stored.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: seabed material extraction area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which materials forming, or under, the seabed are removed.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of oil barrier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of barriers used to prevent the unwanted spread of oil across the sea surface.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: oil retention (high pressure pipe)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a pipe with holes from which air blows. When the air bubbles reach the surface they form a barrier which prevents the spread of oil.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: floating oil barrier
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a floating tube shaped structure, with a curtain (2 metre) hanging under it, below the surface, which prevents the spread of oil.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of pile
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of pile, driven into the earth as a foundation or support for a structure

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stake
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an elongated wood or metal pole embedded in the bottom to serve as a marker or support.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: post
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a vertical piece of timber, metal or concrete forced into the earth or sea bed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tripodal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a single structure comprising 3 or more piles held together (sections of heavy timber, steel or concrete), and forced into the earth or sea bed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: boarding by pilot-cruising vessel
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: pilot boards from a cruising vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: boarding by helicopter
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: pilot boards by helicopter which comes out from the shore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pilot comes out from shore
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: pilot boards from a vessel which comes out from the shore on request.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of pipeline/pipe
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classsification of a pipe systems use

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: outfall pipe
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a pipe (generally a sewer or drainage pipe) discharging in to the sea or a river.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: intake pipe
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a pipe taking water from a river or other body of water, to drive a mill or supply a canal, waterworks, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: sewer
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a pipe in a sewage system for carrying water or sewage to a disposal area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bubbler system
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a submerged pipe from which warm water bubbles, preventing the surrounding water from freezing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: supply pipe
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a pipe used for supplying of gas or liquid product.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of production area
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an area set aside for heavy industry

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: quarry
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an excavation in solid rock from which building stone, limestone, etc. is removed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: mine
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an excavation in the earth for the purpose of extracting earth materials.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: stockpile
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a reserve stock of material, equipment or other supplies.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: power station area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a stationary plant containing apparatus for large-scale conversion of some form of energy (hydraulic, steam, chemical, nuclear, etc.) into electrical energy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: refinery area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a system of process units used to convert crude petroleum into fuels, lubricants and other petroleum-derived products.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: timber yard
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a storage area for wood used for building, carpentry or joinery.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: factory area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a group of buildings where goods are manufactured.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: tank farm
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which a number of large-capacity storage tanks are located, generally used for crude oil or petroleum products.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: wind farm
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which numerous wind motors are located.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: slag heap/spoil heap
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: hill of refuse from a mine, industrial plant etc. on land

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of pylon
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the pylon based on the service its supporting.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: power transmission pylon/pole
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a vertical construction consisting, for example, of a steel framework or of pre-stressed concrete, to support a power transmission cable or line.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: telephone/telegraph pylon/pole
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a pylon or pole used to support a telephone or telegraph line.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: aerial cableway/sky pylon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tower or pylon supporting steel cables which convey cars, buckets, or other suspended carrier units.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bridge pylon/tower
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tower, abutment or pylon from which a bridge deck is suspended.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bridge pier
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a support in the form of a pillar or pier for the spans of a bridge.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of radar station
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of radar station based on the services offered.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: radar surveillance station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a radar station established for traffic surveillance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: coast radar station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a shore-based station which the mariner can contact by radio to obtain a position.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of radar transponder beacon
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of radar transponder beacon based on fuctionality.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ramark, radar beacon transmitting continuously
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a radar marker beacon which continuously transmits a signal appearing as a radial line on a radar screen, the line indicating the direction of the beacon. Ramarks are intended primarily for marine use. The name 'ramark' is derived from the words radar marker.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: racon, radar transponder beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a radar beacon which returns a coded signal which provides identification of the beacon, as well as range and bearing. The range and bearing are indicated by the location of the first character received on the radar screen. The name 'racon' is derived from the words radar beacon.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: leading racon/radar transponder beacon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a radar beacon that may be used (in conjunction with at least one other radar beacon) to indicate a leading line.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of radio station
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of radio services offered by a radio station.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: A radiobeacon is a radio transmitter which emits a distinctive or characteristic signal on which a bearing may be taken.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: radio direction-finding station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a radio station intended to determine only the direction of other stations by means of transmission from the latter.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: decca
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the Decca Navigator System is a high accuracy, short to medium range radio navigational aid intended for coastal and landfall navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: loran C
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: loran-C is a low frequency electronic position fixing system using pulsed transmissions at 100 Khz.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: differential GPS
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a radiobeacon transmitting DGPS correction signals.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: toran
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: toran is an electronic position fixing system used mainly by aircraft.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: omega
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: omega is a long-range radio navigational aid which operates within the VLF frequency band. The system comprises eight land based stations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: syledis
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: syledis is a ranging position fixing system operating at 420-450MHz over a range of up to 400Km.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: chiaka (Chayka)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: chiaka is a low frequency electronic position fixing system using pulsed transmissions at 100 Khz.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: radio telephone station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the equipment needed at one station to carry on two way voice communication by radio waves only.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of recommended track
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of track based on defining navigational marks

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: based on a system of fixed marks
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a straight route (known as a recommended track, range or leading line), which comprises at least two structures (usually beacons or daymarks) and/or natural features, which may carry lights and/or top-marks. The structures/features are positioned so that when observed to be in line, a vessel can follow a known bearing with safety.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: not based on a system of fixed marks
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a route (known as a recommended track or preferred route) which is not based on a series of structures or features in line.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of rescue station
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of aid station based on life saving equipment

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: rescue station with lifeboat
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where equipment for saving life at sea is maintained the type of lifeboat may vary from fast, long distance boats to inflatable inshore boats.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: rescue station with rocket
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: rocket - a pyrotechnic projectile used for signalling or for life-saving purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: refuge for ship-wrecked mariners
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: shelter or protection from danger or distress at sea.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: refuge for intertidal area walkers
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: shelter or protection from danger in areas exposed to extreme and sudden tides or tidal streams.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: lifeboat lying at a mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where a lifeboat is moored ready for use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: aid radio station
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a radio station reserved for emergency situations, might also be a public telephone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: first aid equipment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where first aid equipment is available.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of restricted area
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The area around an offshore installation within which vessels are prohibited from entering without permission. Special regulations protect installations within a safety zone and vessels of all nationalities are required to respect the zone.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The official legal status of each kind of restricted area defines the kind of restriction(s), e.g. the restriction for a "game preserve" may be "entering prohibited", the restriction for an "anchoring prohibition area" is "anchoring prohibited".

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: offshore safety zone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: the area around an offshore installation within which vessels are prohibited from entering without permission special regulations protect installations within a safety zone and vessels of all nationalities are required to respect the zone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: nature reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tract of land managed so as to preserve it's flora, fauna, physical features, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bird sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where birds are bred and protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: game reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where wild animals or birds hunted for sport or food are kept undisturbed for private use.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: seal sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where seals are protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: degaussing range
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area, usually about two cables diameter, within which ships' magnetic fields may be measured sensing instruments and cables are installed on the sea bed in the range and there are cables leading from the range to a control position ashore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: military area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area controlled by the military in which restrictions may apply.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: historic wreck area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area around certain wrecks of historical importance to protect the wrecks from unauthorized interference by diving, salvage or deposition (including anchoring).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: navigational aid safety zone
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area around a navigational aid which vessels are prohibited from entering.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: minefield
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area laid and maintained with explosive mines for defence or practice purposes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: swimming area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which people may swim and therefore vessel movement may be restricted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: waiting area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area reserved for vessels waiting to enter a harbour.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: research area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area where marine research takes place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: dredging area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area where dredging is taking place.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: fish sanctuary
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where fish are protected.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ecological reserve
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a tract of land managed so as to preserve the relation of plants and living creatures to each other and to their surroundings.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: no wake area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area in which a vessels' speed must be reduced in order to reduce the size of the wake it produces.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: swinging area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area where vessels turn.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: recreation area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area within which recreational activities regularly take place and therefore vessel movement may be restricted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: environmentally sensitive sea area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a generic term which may be used to describe a wide range of areas, considered sensitive for a variety of environmental reasons.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: particularly sensitive sea area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area that needs special protection through action by IMO because of its significance for regional ecological, socio-economic or scientific reasons and because it may be vulnerable to damage by international shipping activities.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: disengagement area
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an area near a fairway where vessels can go to clear the way or make an about turn and possibly return to a waiting area when the nautical conditions impose it.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of road
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of a road based on size

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: motorway
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a main road with separate carriageways and limited access, specially constructed and controlled for fast motor traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: major road
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a hard surfaced (metalled) road a main through route.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: minor road
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a secondary road for local traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: track/path
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: track - a rough path or way formed by use path - a way or track laid down for walking or made by continual treading.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: major street
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a main road, in an urban area, for through traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: minor street
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a secondary road, in an urban area, for local traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: crossing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a place where roads, etc. intersect.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of runway
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of runway based on primary aircraft type.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: aeroplane runway
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a level stretch of land where aeroplanes take of and land.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: helicopter landing pad
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a site on which helicopters may land and take off.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Category of sea area
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of an area based on its physical characteristics

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: gat
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a natural or artificial passage or channel through shoals or steep banks, or across a line of banks lying between two channels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bank
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an elevation over which the depth of water is relatively shallow, but normally sufficient for safe surface navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: deep
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: in oceanography, an obsolete term which was generally restricted to depths greater than 6,000 m.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: bay
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an indentation in the coastline.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: trench
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a long narrow, characteristically very deep and asymmetrical depression of the sea floor, with relatively steep sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: basin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a depression, characteristically in the deep sea floor, more or less equidimensional in plan and of variable extent.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: flat
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a level tract of land, as the bed of a dry lake or an area frequently uncovered at low tide. Usually in plural.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: reef
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: rock lying at or near the sea surface that may constitute a hazard to surface navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ledge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a rocky formation continuous with and fringing the shore.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: canyon
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively narrow, deep depression with steep sides, the bottom of which generally has a continuous slope, developed characteristically on some continental slopes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: narrows
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a navigable narrow part of a bay, strait, river, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shoal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an offshore hazard to surface navigation that is composed of unconsolidated material.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: knoll
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a relatively small isolated elevation of a rounded shape.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ridge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: (a) A long, narrow elevation with steep sides. (b) A long, narrow elevation often separating ocean basins. (c) The linked major mid-oceanic mountain systems of global extent.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: seamount
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a large isolated elevation, greater than 1000m in relief above the sea floor, characteristically of conical form.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: pinnacle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: any high tower or spire-shaped pillar or rock or coral, alone or cresting a summit. It may extend above the surface of the water. It may or may not be a hazard to surface navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: abyssal plain
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: an extensive, flat, gently sloping or nearly level region at abyssal depths.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: plateau
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a flat or nearly flat area of considerable extent, dropping off abruptly on one or more sides.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: spur
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a subordinate elevation, ridge or rise projecting outward from a larger feature.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: shelf
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a zone adjacent to a continent (or around an island) and extending from the low water line to a depth at which there is usually a marked increase of slope towards oceanic depths.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: trough
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a long depression of the sea floor characteristically flat bottomed and steep sided and normally shallower than a trench.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: saddle
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: a broad pass, resembling in shape a riding saddle, in a ridge or between contiguous seamounts.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: abyssal hills
